# Code Review Checklist

## Scope: New and Changed Code Only

**Review ONLY the lines that are new or modified in the current change.** Do not flag pre-existing issues in untouched code. If old code surrounding the change has violations, note them as "Pre-existing (out of scope)" — do not demand they be fixed in the same PR. The only exception is P0 security issues (token exposure, missing sanitization) which should always be flagged regardless of scope.

When reviewing, evaluate every applicable section below. Report violations with exact file path, line number, severity, and a concrete fix. Mark each section PASS, FAIL, or N/A.

**Severity levels**: P0 (security/data loss) > P1 (correctness/crash) > P2 (performance) > P3 (maintainability) > P4 (style)

---

## 1. TypeScript & Type Safety [P1]

- [ ] No new `any` without a `// TODO: type this` comment — prefer `unknown` + type guard
- [ ] No `as any` or `as unknown as X` without a justification comment
- [ ] No unused variables, imports, or parameters — build fails (`noUnusedLocals`, `noUnusedParameters`)
- [ ] Exported functions have explicit return types
- [ ] Types co-located with feature (`types.ts` in slice/service directory), not dumped globally
- [ ] Reuses existing enums (`HTTPMethods`, `TokenTypes`, `ENV`) — no duplicate magic strings
- [ ] No `moment` imports — use `dayjs` and `@/utils/datetime` for all new date code
- [ ] No imports from unused dependencies (`@tiptap/*`, `lottie-react`, `embla-carousel-react`)
- [ ] No TS7006 in changed lines — callback parameters (`.map()`, `.filter()`, `.reduce()`, event handlers) must be explicitly typed when inference is unclear

## 2. Import Hygiene [P4]

- [ ] Import order: builtin > external > @/ internal > parent > sibling > styles (ESLint error)
- [ ] Blank line between each import group
- [ ] `@/*` path alias for anything in `src/` — no `../../../` deep relative paths
- [ ] No unused imports
- [ ] SCSS/CSS imports are last
- [ ] No barrel imports pulling entire libraries — use named imports

## 3. SSR Safety [P1]

- [ ] No bare `window`, `document`, `navigator`, `localStorage`, `sessionStorage` access without `typeof window !== 'undefined'` guard
- [ ] Uses `@/utils/storageManager` for cookie/localStorage/sessionStorage — not direct `window.localStorage`
- [ ] `useEffect` used for browser-only side effects — never in module scope or render body
- [ ] Components using browser APIs have `'use client'` directive
- [ ] No `window.location` mutations outside event handlers or effects

## 4. React & Component Quality [P2]

- [ ] `'use client'` only on components that need hooks, events, or browser APIs
- [ ] No business logic inside JSX return — extract to `useMemo`, variables, or hooks above return
- [ ] `useCallback` wraps handlers passed as props to children or in `useEffect` deps
- [ ] `useMemo` wraps expensive computations: column definitions, sorted/filtered large lists, heavy transformations
- [ ] `useMemo` NOT overused on trivial expressions (`x ?? {}`, boolean checks, string concat, simple casts)
- [ ] `React.memo` on row/cell components rendered in `.map()` for lists > 20 items
- [ ] `key` prop uses stable unique ID — never array index on dynamic/reorderable lists
- [ ] No inline object/array literals as props to `React.memo` children (breaks memoization)
- [ ] `useEffect` has correct dependency array — no missing deps, no unnecessary deps
- [ ] `useEffect` with timers/subscriptions/listeners returns a cleanup function
- [ ] No empty `useEffect(() => {}, [deps])` — this is dead code
- [ ] Component files under 300 lines — split into sub-components if larger
- [ ] Heavy components (modals, charts) use `next/dynamic` with `{ ssr: false }` where needed

## 5. State Management [P2]

- [ ] Local UI state (`useState`) vs shared state (Redux) correctly separated
- [ ] RTK Query for all server data — no `fetch` + `useEffect` + `useState` pattern
- [ ] RTK Query mutations define `invalidatesTags` — no stale cache after writes
- [ ] Selectors from `selectors.ts` — no inline `useSelector(state => state.x.y)` in components
- [ ] No direct store imports in components — use `useSelector`, `useDispatch`, RTK Query hooks
- [ ] No Redux dispatch for data that should be RTK Query cache

## 6. API Layer [P1]

- [ ] New endpoints use `api.injectEndpoints()` or `noTokenApi.injectEndpoints()`
- [ ] Uses `HTTPMethods` enum — not `'POST'` string
- [ ] URL built with `joinPath()` + constants from `@/services/constants`
- [ ] `FormData` body is NOT wrapped in `JSON.stringify()`
- [ ] Error states handled — `isError` checked, user notified via `showToast`
- [ ] No raw `fetch()` calls (only exception: `api.ts` token refresh)
- [ ] No sensitive data (tokens, passwords, PII) in `console.log`
- [ ] Response transformation in `@/utils/responseModifiers` — not inline in components

## 7. Internationalization [P3]

- [ ] All user-facing strings use `useTranslations()` — zero hardcoded English in JSX
- [ ] Translation key added to all three locale files: `en.json`, `ro.json`, `bg.json`
- [ ] Namespace matches feature: `useTranslations('Roster')`, `useTranslations('Common')`
- [ ] Date/time display uses project formatters from `@/utils/datetime` or `@/utils/formatters`
- [ ] Validation messages, toast messages, button labels, placeholders — all translated
- [ ] No new hardcoded strings added (existing ones are tracked technical debt)

## 8. Styling [P4]

- [ ] No Tailwind classes — project uses Mantine + SCSS Modules
- [ ] Component styles in co-located `*.module.scss` — not global CSS
- [ ] Colors use `Colors.xxx` from `@/app/style/colors` or Mantine theme — no raw hex values
- [ ] Inline `style={{}}` only for truly dynamic runtime values (drag positions, transforms)
- [ ] Responsive uses Mantine breakpoint PostCSS variables — no hardcoded `px` media queries
- [ ] New colors added to `Colors` class, not scattered as local constants

## 9. Security [P0]

- [ ] No tokens, keys, or secrets hardcoded — environment variables only
- [ ] Every `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` wrapped with `DOMPurify.sanitize()`
- [ ] Passwords encrypted via `encryptPassword()` before API transmission
- [ ] No `eval()`, `new Function()`, `innerHTML` assignment, or dynamic script injection
- [ ] User-provided data escaped/sanitized before rendering
- [ ] New protected routes added to middleware matcher pattern
- [ ] No tokens stored in localStorage/sessionStorage — cookies only
- [ ] No sensitive data in URL query parameters

## 10. Routing & Navigation [P3]

- [ ] Route paths from `@/routes` constants — no hardcoded strings
- [ ] New pages placed in correct route group: `(wfm)`, `(hr)`, `(training)`
- [ ] Page has `'use client'` if interactive
- [ ] Layout created if page needs shared UI (sidebar tabs, subnav)
- [ ] Navigation guard applied if page has forms with unsaved changes
- [ ] `trailingSlash` convention respected in any programmatic navigation

## 11. Performance [P2]

- [ ] No unnecessary re-renders — memoization applied where parent re-renders cascade
- [ ] Dynamic imports for heavy components not visible on initial render
- [ ] Images use `next/image` with explicit `width`/`height` — no raw `<img>` tags
- [ ] No synchronous blocking in render (no `JSON.parse` of large payloads, no heavy loops)
- [ ] Named imports from libraries — no `import * as` or full-library imports
- [ ] No new `moment` usage — use `dayjs` (moment is 300KB+ full-locale)

## 12. Error Handling [P1]

- [ ] API calls: RTK Query `isError` checked OR try/catch with `showToast`
- [ ] No silent error swallowing — every catch block logs or notifies
- [ ] `useEffect` async operations wrapped in try/catch
- [ ] Optional chaining `?.` on API response data that may be null/undefined
- [ ] No unhandled promise rejections — `.catch()` on promises or try/catch on await
- [ ] Consider adding `error.tsx` for new page routes (currently zero exist)

## 13. Code Cleanliness & Simplicity [P3]

- [ ] No `console.log` — remove before commit (20+ already exist as tech debt, don't add more)
- [ ] No commented-out code blocks — use git history
- [ ] No TODO/FIXME without ticket reference or expiration
- [ ] Functions under 50 lines — extract helpers for complex logic
- [ ] Descriptive names: `isLoading` not `loading`, `hasError` not `error` for booleans
- [ ] No dead code paths or unreachable branches
- [ ] No nested ternary operators — use `if/else` or early returns for multiple conditions
- [ ] Clarity over brevity — prefer explicit readable code over dense one-liners that require mental parsing
- [ ] No unnecessary abstractions — don't wrap a function in another function if it adds no value

## 14. Accessibility [P3]

- [ ] Interactive elements have visible labels or `aria-label`
- [ ] Custom clickable `<div>`/`<span>` have `role="button"` + `onKeyDown` handler
- [ ] Form inputs have labels via Mantine's `label` prop or `aria-label`
- [ ] Status indicators use icon + text, not color alone
- [ ] Tab order makes sense — no `tabIndex` hacks

## 15. Testing [P3] (If Applicable)

- [ ] New shared component has a smoke test (renders without crash)
- [ ] Tests use `getByRole` > `getByLabelText` > `getByText` — `getByTestId` is last resort
- [ ] Mocks scoped to test — no global mock leakage
- [ ] Test co-located: `Component.test.tsx` in same directory
- [ ] No snapshot tests — they add noise, not confidence
- [ ] Test clarity over DRY — scenario-specific props/state visible inside each test, not hidden in shared setup
- [ ] Shared `beforeEach` only when 3+ tests genuinely share identical setup
- [ ] Static "default render" assertions consolidated into one smoke test

## 16. Dependency Management [P1]

- [ ] No new `npm install` or `package.json` changes without explicit developer approval
- [ ] Before suggesting a new package, verify no existing dependency already covers the need
- [ ] No version bumps or lockfile changes unless specifically requested

---

## Review Output Format

```
### [Section Name] — PASS / FAIL / N/A

**P0 FAIL** [src/services/newService.ts:45] Token logged to console
→ Remove `console.log(token)` — sensitive data exposure

**P2 FAIL** [src/app/mgt/(hr)/feature/page.tsx:120] Missing useMemo on filtered list
→ Wrap `data.filter(...)` in `useMemo(() => ..., [data])`

**P4 FAIL** [src/app/mgt/(hr)/feature/page.tsx:89] Hardcoded hex color
→ Use `Colors.primaryColor` from `@/app/style/colors`
```

Report P0 and P1 issues first. These must be fixed before merge. P2-P4 can be addressed in follow-up if non-blocking.
